# /home/wildlife
msgid ""
"Beavers are becoming more common across the UK. These large, semi-aquatic "
"rodents have brown fur, a flat paddle-like tail and can sometimes be seen "
"swimming or eating willow on the riverbank. You’re most likely to spot them "
"at dawn or at dusk."
msgstr ""
"Mae afancod yn dod yn fwy cyffredin ledled y DU. Mae gan y cnofilod mawr, "
"lled-ddyfrol hyn ffwr brown a chynffon fflat fel padl.  Gallwch eu gweld "
"weithiau yn nofio neu'n bwyta helyg ar lan yr afon. Rydych chi'n fwyaf "
"tebygol o'u gweld gyda'r wawr neu gyda'r nos."

# /home/wildlife
msgid ""
"Coots are also medium-sized and have dark black feathers, but they have a "
"bright white bill and white feathers that extends backwards over their "
"forehead."
msgstr ""
"Mae cwtieir yn ganolig eu maint.  Mae eu plu yn ddu yn bennaf ac mae "
"ganddynt big gwyn llachar a phlu gwyn sy'n ymestyn yn ôl dros eu talcen."

# /home/wildlife
msgid ""
"Dippers are small, dark brown birds with a white breast patch that extends "
"down their throat. They can often be seen standing and bobbing up and down "
"on rocks on the water’s edge in fast-flowing rivers, where they search for "
"insects."
msgstr ""
"Mae trochwyr yn adar bach, brown tywyll gyda patsh gwyn ar y frest sy'n "
"ymestyn i lawr eu gwddf. Gellir eu gweld yn aml yn sefyll ac yn siglo i fyny"
" ac i lawr ar greigiau ar ymyl y dŵr mewn afonydd cyflym, lle maent yn "
"chwilio am bryfed."

# /home/wildlife
msgid ""
"By a river in the summer, you might spot a variety of different sized and "
"coloured dragonflies and dameselflies; These are thin insects with dark "
"wings, large heads and long abdomens and are often seen hovering and flying "
"over and around the water. The wings on a resting dragonfly extend out to "
"the sides of their body, while the wings on a resting damselfly, which are "
"normally smaller and more delicate, reach backwards in line with their long "
"bodies."
msgstr ""
"Wrth afon yn yr haf, efallai y gwelwch amrywiaeth o weision neidr a "
"mursennod o wahanol faint a lliw.  Mae’r rhain yn bryfed tenau gydag adenydd"
" tywyll, pennau mawr ac abdomenau hir.  Maent i’w gweld yn aml yn hofran ac "
"yn hedfan dros ac o gwmpas y dŵr. Mae'r adenydd ar was y neidr sy'n gorffwys"
" yn ymestyn allan i ochrau ei gorff, tra bod yr adenydd ar fursen sy'n "
"gorffwys, sydd fel arfer yn llai ac yn fwy eiddil, yn ymestyn yn ôl yn unol "
"â'u cyrff hir."

# /home/wildlife
msgid ""
"Ducks are common in many waterways. There are many different species of "
"duck, each with large bills, short necks and webbed feet. The mallard is one"
" of the UK’s best-known ducks; males have a distinctive green head, and "
"females are brown."
msgstr ""
"Mae hwyaid yn gyffredin mewn llawer o ddyfrffyrdd.  Mae llawer o rywogaethau"
" o hwyaden, pob un gyda phig mawr, gwddf byr a thraed gweog.  Yr hwyaden "
"wyllt yw un o'r hwyaid mwyaf adnabyddus yn y DU.  Mae gan y gwrywod ben "
"gwyrdd nodweddiadol ac mae'r benywod yn frown. "

# /home/wildlife
msgid ""
"A large number of different fish species can be found in rivers in the UK "
"and Ireland. They vary in size and shape, and it is not always possible to "
"identify them just by sight from the riverbank. So, for this survey, simply "
"record whether you saw any fish or not during your river observation."
msgstr ""
"Mae nifer fawr o rywogaethau pysgod gwahanol i'w cael mewn afonydd yn y DU "
"ac Iwerddon. Maent yn amrywio o ran maint a siâp, ac nid yw bob amser yn "
"bosibl eu hadnabod wrth eu gweld o lan yr afon. Felly, at ddibenion yr "
"arolwg hwn, cofnodwch a welsoch chi unrhyw bysgodyn ai peidio wrth arsylwi'r"
" afon."

# /home/wildlife
msgid ""
"These small birds have slate grey plumage on their upper parts, but their "
"underside is a vibrant yellow. Grey wagtails nest near fast-flowing water "
"and eat insects found at the river edge."
msgstr ""
"Mae gan yr adar bach hyn blu llwydlas ar eu rhannau uchaf, ond mae eu hochr "
"isaf yn felyn llachar. Mae siglennod llwyd yn nythu ger dŵr sy'n llifo'n "
"gyflym ac yn bwyta pryfed a geir ar ymyl yr afon."

# /home/wildlife
msgid ""
"Herons are large birds, reaching up to a meter in height and you’re unlikely"
" to mistake them for another species. They have mainly grey plumage, long "
"yellow legs and a long neck leading to a pointed yellow bill."
msgstr ""
"Mae crehyrod yn adar mawr, sy’n cyrraedd hyd at fetr o daldra. Mae’n "
"annhebygol y byddwch yn eu camgymryd am rywogaeth arall. Mae ganddynt blu "
"llwyd yn bennaf, coesau hir melyn a gwddf hir sy'n arwain at big melyn "
"pigfain."

# /home/wildlife
msgid ""
"These small, fast-flying birds are always a treat to see. Their bright blue "
"and orange bodies add a splash of colour as they perch on branches, or dart "
"quickly into the water to catch fish with their long black bills."
msgstr ""
"Mae'n hyfryd bob amser gweld yr adar bach hyn sy'n hedfan yn gyflym.  Mae eu"
" cyrff glas ac oren llachar yn ychwanegu sblash o liw wrth iddynt glwydo ar "
"ganghennau, neu wibio'n gyflym i mewn i'r dŵr i ddal pysgod gyda'u pigau du "
"hir. "

# /home/wildlife
msgid ""
"Collectively known as ‘riverflies’, the larvae of these winged insects spend"
" most of their life in the river, where they are a great food source for "
"large fish. They emerge as flying adults for just a short period of time to "
"reproduce. They are often under 3 cm in size. Many of the riverflies  are "
"not tolerant of pollution, so their presence can be used as an indicator of "
"good water quality."
msgstr ""
"Yn cael eu hadnabod gyda’i gilydd fel ‘pryfed afon’.  Mae larfa’r pryfed "
"asgellog hyn yn treulio’r rhan fwyaf o’u hoes yn yr afon ac maent yn "
"ffynhonnell fwyd wych i bysgod mawr. Maent yn ymddangos fel oedolion sy'n "
"hedfan am gyfnod byr yn unig i atgenhedlu. Maent yn aml yn llai na 3cm o "
"faint. Nid yw llawer o bryfed yr afon yn gallu goddef llygredd, felly mae eu"
" presenoldeb yn arwydd o ansawdd dŵr da."

# /home/wildlife
msgid ""
"Moorhens are about the size of a duck, but are largely black with a bright "
"red and yellow beak, with long green legs and un-webbed feet."
msgstr ""
"Mae ieir dŵr tua'r un maint â hwyaid. Mae eu plu'n ddu yn bennaf ac mae "
"ganddynt big coch a melyn llachar a choesau hir gwyrdd. Nid yw eu traed yn "
"weog."

# /home/wildlife
msgid ""
"Otters appear brown or grey, have slimmer bodies than beavers and a long "
"thin tail. They’re a top predator in a river habitat, can be playful and are"
" very fast swimmers with an impressive ability to hold their breath "
"underwater."
msgstr ""
"Mae dyfrgwn yn frown neu'n llwyd.  Mae ganddynt gyrff teneuach nag afancod a"
" chynffon hir denau. Maent yn brif ysglyfaethwr mewn cynefin afon. Gallant "
"fod yn chwareus ac maent yn nofwyr cyflym iawn gyda gallu trawiadol i ddal "
"eu hanadl o dan y dŵr."

# /home/wildlife
msgid ""
"Rats are strong swimmers and can often be found around rivers, particularly "
"in urban waterways. They are brown with short fur, a pointy face and a long "
"pink tail. Rats can carry some human diseases and so it is important to "
"always wash hands carefully after being in contact with river water."
msgstr ""
"Mae llygod mawr yn nofwyr cryf a gellir eu gweld yn aml o gwmpas afonydd, yn"
" enwedig dyfrffyrdd trefol.  Maent yn frown gyda blew cwta, wyneb main a "
"chynffon hir binc.  Gall llygod mawr gario rhai clefydau dynol, felly mae'n "
"bwysig bob amser i olchi eich dwylo'n ofalus ar ôl bod mewn cysylltiad â dŵr"
" afon."

# /home/wildlife
msgid ""
"Swans are large white waterbirds, with elongated s-shaped necks, often "
"orange bills and a large wingspan. You might also see younger swans, known "
"as cygnets, which are grey/brown in colour before they turn white."
msgstr ""
"Mae elyrch yn adar dŵr mawr gwyn, gyda gwddf hirfain siâp s, pig oren yn aml"
" a lled esgyll mawr.  Efallai y gwelwch gywion elyrch hefyd sy'n llwyd neu "
"frown cyn iddynt droi'n wyn."

# /home/pollution
msgid ""
"There are many different types of pollution that can be found in our "
"waterways. Some, like chemicals and nutrients are hard to identify, but "
"others are easier to see. Here are a few examples of the more common types "
"of pollution."
msgstr ""
"Mae llawer o wahanol fathau o lygredd i'w gweld yn ein dyfrffyrdd. Mae rhai "
"fel cemegion a maetholion yn anodd eu hadnabod, ond mae eraill yn haws i'w "
"gweld. Dyma ychydig enghreifftiau o'r mathau mwyaf cyffredin o lygredd."

